File: City Power is currently determining the cause of the fire. JOHANNESBURG - A fire at the Cleveland substation destroyed a transformer on Christmas Eve. The fire left some Joburg residents without power on Christmas Day. City Power is currently determining the cause of the fire. WATCH: No light at the end of the load-shedding tunnel Areas in darkness include Kensington, Jeppestown, Malvern, Heriotdale, Denver and Benrose. The fire was extinguished early on Christmas morning. It's reported that repairs will only be completed by Thursday evening.